The exact generated class name must match your project. In the screenshot it appears similar to:

```java
PartnersBeAp74737ResourceTypeApi
```

Use IntelliJ auto-import for the precise spelling.

### Verifying the bearer token

Your generated `ApiClient` may not expose a `getBearerToken()` method. If it does, add:

```java
assertEquals("test-token", result.getBearerToken());
```

If it does not, do not use reflection merely for coverage. Testing the branch by invoking the method is sufficient for JaCoCo.

