## 3. `PingScimPropertiesTest`

Because it is a record, one constructor/accessor test covers the generated record methods that Sonar is reporting.

```java
package com.bnpp.pf.partner.repository.ping.config;

import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertEquals;
import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertFalse;

import java.time.Duration;

import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;

class PingScimPropertiesTest {

    @Test
    void shouldExposeConfiguredProperties() {
        Duration connectTimeout = Duration.ofSeconds(5);
        Duration readTimeout = Duration.ofSeconds(10);

        PingScimProperties properties =
                new PingScimProperties(
                        false,
                        "https://ping.example.com",
                        "username",
                        "password",
                        "bearer-token",
                        connectTimeout,
                        readTimeout
                );

        assertFalse(properties.enabled());
        assertEquals(
                "https://ping.example.com",
                properties.baseUrl()
        );
        assertEquals("username", properties.username());
        assertEquals("password", properties.password());
        assertEquals(
                "bearer-token",
                properties.bearerToken()
        );
        assertEquals(
                connectTimeout,
                properties.connectTimeout()
        );
        assertEquals(
                readTimeout,
                properties.readTimeout()
        );
    }
}
```

This test is acceptable, although testing configuration records has relatively low business value. It is mainly useful because Sonar currently includes the record in coverage calculation.

