# Small production-code optimization

Your configuration currently has:

```java
if (properties.bearerToken() != null
        && !properties.bearerToken().isBlank()) {
    apiClient.setBearerToken(properties.bearerToken());
}
```

You can make it slightly cleaner by storing the value once:

```java
@Bean
public ApiClient pingApiClient(
        PingScimProperties properties
) {
    ApiClient apiClient = new ApiClient();
    apiClient.setBasePath(properties.baseUrl());

    String bearerToken = properties.bearerToken();

    if (bearerToken != null && !bearerToken.isBlank()) {
        apiClient.setBearerToken(bearerToken);
    }

    return apiClient;
}
```

This avoids calling the accessor three times and makes the test branches clearer.

A more reusable version would be:

```java
private boolean hasText(String value) {
    return value != null && !value.isBlank();
}
```

But for one condition, the local variable is enough.

