# Optional: exclude pure configuration properties from coverage

If your team does not require tests for simple records or generated/configuration classes, you can exclude them from JaCoCo or Sonar. For example:

```xml
<configuration>
    <excludes>
        <exclude>
            **/config/*Properties.class
        </exclude>
        <exclude>
            **/ping/client/generated/**
        </exclude>
    </excludes>
</configuration>
```

Do not exclude:

```text
UserSynchronizationService
UserService
PingUserClient
PingUserMapper
```

Those contain real business behavior and should be tested.

The next highest-value target is `UserSynchronizationService`, since it has 118 uncovered lines and 34 uncovered branches. That class will require scenario-based tests rather than simple coverage tests.
